# 1. Create a new repo at github.com, then:
git init ai-stock-trader
cd ai-stock-trader

# 2. Drop all the downloaded files in here, then:
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit: AI stock trader powered by Claude + Alpaca"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/ai-stock-trader.git
git push -u origin main
```

The repo structure is:
```
ai-stock-trader/
├── ai_trader.py        ← all the logic
├── README.md           ← full docs with usage examples
├── requirements.txt    ← pip dependencies
├── .env.template       ← copy to .env, add your keys
└── .gitignore          ← keeps .env and __pycache__ out of git
